05/09/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Albania stunned reigning European champion Greece in the first round of World Cup qualifiers on Saturday (4 September) with an unexpected 2-1 win at home. Fans filled the streets of Albanian towns, celebrating their country's biggest sports victory in recent years. Turkey suffered an unexpected setback, managing only a 1-1 draw at home against Georgia. Ireland crushed Cyprus 3-0, while Croatia beat Hungary by the same score at home. Romania defeated Macedonia 2-1 at home. Serbia-Montenegro started its World Cup campaign with a 3-0 win at San Marino. Bulgaria also made an impressive start, with a 3-1 win in Reykjavik against Iceland. (AP, Reuters, AFP, Bloomberg - 04/09/04)
